@Justin 

Benching a player in sports happens in Polish too, in the expression "odesłać na ławkę" (literally, to send somebody onto the bench). 

In a legal context, we use the word ława (bench/pew) when talking about your jury - in Polish we call it "ława przysięgłych", "bench/pew of jurors". Our legal system does not include juries, nor do we use the word bench to describe anything else in that system.

@Suzanne 
